}
// The main function remains unchanged.

```


This way, the vector manages the dynamically allocated memory and ensures that it is deallocated properly when the array is destroyed.

It sounds like you need to adjust the styles specifically for mobile and potentially add some styling to the image containment. Try isolating the image and giving it a fixed wrapping element to prevent overlapping, like so:

```css
@media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
  .product__info-container {
    padding: 10px;
  }
  .product__image-container {
    max-width: 100%; /* Ensure image doesn't exceed parent's width */
    margin-bottom: 15px; /* Add some space between the image and text */
  }
  .product__title {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
  }
  .product__description {
    margin-top: 15px;
  }
}
```

You'll also need to ensure that the HTML correctly contains the image within a div with the `.product__image-container` class for this solution to work.

